Long distance relationships can be tricky. From students to people who work abroad, people from different backgrounds have tried to make it work. Some couples go one step further, when one person moves to their partner’s country. With the effects of Brexit unfolding and more restrictions set to be placed on who can travel and where to, romantic relationships between people from different European countries are likely to be affected. We would like to hear from readers who have moved across Europe for love. Which country are you from and which country did you move to? How did you decide who would move? Did you enjoy living in that country and are you still together? In light of Brexit, do you have any concerns about staying in Europe? You can get in touch by filling in the encrypted form below. Only the Guardian will see your responses and one of our journalists may be in touch for more information. If you’re having trouble using the form, click here. Read terms of service here.